        <p class="AdvisoryBoardFull-content">
          My passion is to educate, inspire and empower those in need of healing or those who simply want to feel better to live a happier and healthier life.
        </p>
        <p class="AdvisoryBoardFull-content"> 
          Understanding and helping others achieve optimal health, both mind and body have always been a love of mine.  I have worked in the healthcare industry for over 30 years, working from pediatrics to geriatrics, all with different challenges.  Unfortunately, several year ago, like many others, I experienced some very untimely and personal losses and I couldn’t understand why so many people were getting sick and not being able to recover. The feeling of helplessness was overwhelming.  I began to read everything I could get my hands on in an attempt to understand what was happening. What I discovered, and am still discovering today, was how fascinating the human body is, how it is developed to be strong and self-healing and what we can do every day to help our bodies to heal and repair itself. Our bodies can heal itself as long as we provide it with the right environment.  My passion is educating the many ways in which we can support our bodies to act in the miraculous way it was intended.  Eating and juicing real whole foods and cleansing our bodies at the cellular level is just one of the many ways we can achieve this.
        </p>
        <p class="AdvisoryBoardFull-content">
          My educational background includes a Bachelor of Science degree in Psychology and a Master’s of Science degree in Health and Hospital Administration.  I am certified as a Holistic Nutrition Specialist and a Level II Reiki Practitioner.  
        </p>
