        <h4>Dr. Carol DeFrança</h4>
        <p class="AdvisoryBoardFull-content">
          Dr. Carol DeFrança is a practicing health and wellness clinician who is compassionate,
          down to earth and always willing to help. She and her husband, Dr. Scott Chapman,
          have provided conservative functional medicine to the South Shore and surrounding
          communities for 25 years. Enhance Integrated Wellness, located in Hingham, is where
          their combined experiences have allowed them to create an incredible resource for
          residents of the South Shore. She has expertise in multiple health disciplines and has
          lectured extensively across the United States, Great Britain and Europe on topics that
          include orthopedics, rehabilitation of sports related injuries and clinical nutrition all the
          while, practicing what she preaches.
        </p>
        <p class="AdvisoryBoardFull-content">
          Dr. DeFrança loves to increase her knowledge base and technical skill evidenced by
          hundreds of hours of post graduate training across the United States, Italy, Great
          Britain, and the Czech Republic, to name a few. Her undergraduate education at
          Rutgers University afforded her a Bachelor of Science in Environmental Science and
          Biology. Graduate education at the National University of Health Sciences provided her
          with a Bachelor of Science in Human Biology, Doctorate in Chiropractic and upon
          completion of her three year residency, a Board Certification in Chiropractic
          Orthopedics.
        </p>
        <p class="AdvisoryBoardFull-content">
          The diversity of Dr.DeFrança’s training enables her to approach health and wellness
          challenges in a very individualized and team approach. She sees her patients as a whole,
          not just their injuries or ailments. Her intellectual curiosity enables her to be open to
          creating a health plan allowing them to return to a highly functioning level as quickly as
          possible.
        </p>
        <p class="AdvisoryBoardFull-content">
          Dr. DeFrança is an involved mother and #1 fan of her two children, Carly and Luke.
          She greatly enjoys (regardless of mild frustration) teaching them how to live a healthier
          lifestyle. She currently serves in varying capacities at her home church, North River
          Community Church in Pembroke. She takes great pleasure in both indoor and outdoor
          exercise, reading, pottery, and creating gourmet meals with and for family and friends.
        </p>
